    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1931-10-08T07:00:00-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1931-10-08T07:00:00-05:00" n="148"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d148">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">793.94/2010: Telegram</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The Minister in China</hi> (<persName type="from">
                        <hi rend="italic">Johnson</hi>
                    </persName>) <hi rend="italic">to the <gloss type="to">Secretary of
                            State</gloss>
                    </hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Peiping</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1931-10-08T20:00:00+08:00"
                            >October 8, 1931—8 p.m.</date>
                        <lb/>[Received October 8—6:45 a.m.]</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>729. Following information just received from [apparent omission] of Young
                    Marshal’s office: <quote rend="blockquote">
                        <p>“Between 1 and 2:15 this p.m., 12 Japanese airplanes flew over Chinchow,
                            new seat of the Chinese Provincial Government in Manchuria and dropped
                            36 bombs, chiefly directly [<hi rend="italic">directed?</hi>] at the
                            University buildings and house [of the?] Provincial Government.
                            Buildings were damaged but casualties so far unknown. A bomb was dropped
                            on service car number 141, killing two Chinese cleaners, and <pb
                                facs="0254" n="144" xml:id="pg_144"/> one was dropped on the
                            locomotive sheds. Telegraph lines between Chinchow and Shanhaikwan
                            interrupted.”</p>
                    </quote>
                </p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Johnson</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
    </text>
